# Responsive Design (Mobile-First)

**MANDATORY**: All components MUST be mobile-first and responsive.

## Core Principle: Mobile-First

Always start with mobile styles as the base, then enhance for larger screens using `min-width` media queries.

**Why Mobile-First?**
- Better performance (smaller base CSS)
- Progressive enhancement approach
- Ensures mobile experience is never an afterthought
- Easier to maintain and scale

## Standard Breakpoints

The project uses a single primary breakpoint:

- **Mobile (Base)**: Default styles, no media query needed
- **Tablet/Desktop**: `@media (min-width: 768px)`

**Breakpoint Usage**:
```svelte
<style>
  /* Mobile styles (base) */
  .component {
    padding: 1rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  /* Desktop styles (enhancement) */
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .component {
      padding: 2rem;
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      flex-direction: row;
    }
  }
</style>
```

## Required Responsive Patterns

### 1. Mobile-First Media Queries

**ALWAYS** use `min-width` media queries (mobile-first approach):

```svelte
<style>
  /* ✅ CORRECT: Mobile-first */
  .container {
    padding: 1rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .container {
      padding: 2rem;
    }
  }

  /* ❌ WRONG: Desktop-first */
  .container {
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .container {
      padding: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
```

### 2. Responsive Typography

Use `clamp()` for fluid typography that scales smoothly:

```svelte
<style>
  .headline {
    /* clamp(min, preferred, max) */
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
  }

  .body-text {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.25rem);
  }
</style>
```

**Real Example** (from Hero component):
```svelte
.hero-headline {
  font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 8vw, 4.5rem);
}
```

### 3. Responsive Layouts

**Flexbox with Direction Changes**:
```svelte
<style>
  .flex-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .flex-container {
      flex-direction: row;
      gap: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
```

**CSS Grid with Responsive Columns**:
```svelte
<style>
  .grid-container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .grid-container {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
```

### 4. Responsive Spacing

Adjust padding and margins for different screen sizes:

```svelte
<style>
  .section {
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .section {
      padding: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 3rem;
    }
  }
</style>
```

### 5. Responsive Navigation

Hide/show elements based on viewport:

```svelte
<style>
  /* Mobile: Show hamburger, hide desktop nav */
  .mobile-menu-button {
    display: flex;
  }

  .desktop-nav {
    display: none;
  }

  /* Desktop: Hide hamburger, show desktop nav */
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .mobile-menu-button {
      display: none;
    }

    .desktop-nav {
      display: flex;
    }
  }
</style>
```

### 6. Touch Target Sizes

Ensure interactive elements are at least 44x44px on mobile:

```svelte
<style>
  .button {
    min-height: 44px;
    min-width: 44px;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .button {
      padding: 0.75rem 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
```

### 7. Responsive Images and Media

Use responsive image techniques:

```svelte
<img
  src="image.jpg"
  alt="Description"
  loading="lazy"
  style="width: 100%; height: auto;"
/>
```

## Common Responsive Patterns

### Pattern 1: Stack to Row Layout

```svelte
<style>
  .card-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .card-grid {
      flex-direction: row;
      gap: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
```

### Pattern 2: Responsive Text Alignment

```svelte
<style>
  .text {
    text-align: left;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .text {
      text-align: center;
    }
  }
</style>
```

### Pattern 3: Responsive Width Constraints

```svelte
<style>
  .container {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 0 1rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .container {
      max-width: 1200px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
```

### Pattern 4: Responsive Visibility

```svelte
<style>
  .mobile-only {
    display: block;
  }

  .desktop-only {
    display: none;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .mobile-only {
      display: none;
    }

    .desktop-only {
      display: block;
    }
  }
</style>
```

## Testing Responsiveness

When implementing responsive design:

1. **Test Mobile Viewport**: Check at 375px width (iPhone SE size)
2. **Test Desktop Viewport**: Check at ≥768px width
3. **Check for Horizontal Scrolling**: Ensure no content overflows viewport
4. **Test Touch Interactions**: Verify buttons/links are easily tappable
5. **Test Both Themes**: Check light and dark modes at all breakpoints

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

**❌ Desktop-First Approach**:
```svelte
/* Don't do this */
.component {
  padding: 2rem;
}

@media (max-width: 767px) {
  .component {
    padding: 1rem;
  }
}
```

**❌ Fixed Widths Without Max-Width**:
```svelte
/* Don't do this */
.component {
  width: 1200px;
}
```

**❌ Ignoring Mobile Touch Targets**:
```svelte
/* Don't do this */
.button {
  padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem; /* Too small for mobile */
}
```

